    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#VM">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name>Ἀλκιμίδαι</name></persName>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note>Text after Arena (IGASM 2)</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <p>To Alkimides.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it">
                <p>Per Alkimides.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p>According to Arena, this could be either a singular dative of the name Ἀλκιμίδης or a plural nominative, thus referring to a clan of dedicators (cf. Ἡρακλεῖδαι). 
                    Agostiniani (1999), on the other hand, is inclined towards a feminine noun with an -αι ending typical of the Elymian texts found in Grotta Vanella, Segesta.</p>
            </div>
